brief_summary: To evaluate, in asymptomatic and symptomatic participants with peripheral arterial disease, the feasibility of recruitment and adherence, efficacy and safety of HDL-C raising along with effective control of LDL-C levels, antioxidant therapy, antithrombotic therapy, and their combinations.
condition: Arterial Occlusive Diseases Cardiovascular Diseases Heart Diseases Vascular Diseases Diabetes Mellitus
eligibility_criteria: Men and women with symptomatic or asymptomatic peripheral arterial disease.
